  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (3a15fe9 2023-01-29T00:11:51.291099Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHello,\r\n\r\nusing a mnemonic like:\r\n`rugueux véloce régulier prairie ....`\r\n\r\nrunning following solidity code:\r\n```solidity\r\nstring memory mnemonic = vm.envString(\"MNEMONIC\");\r\naddress deployer = vm.addr(vm.deriveKey(mnemonic, 0));\r\n        \r\n```\r\n\r\nI get the following : \r\n\r\n```solidity \r\n[FAIL. Reason: the word `rugueux` is invalid] testAccount() (gas: 7518)\r\nTraces:\r\n  [7518] Mangrove::testAccount() \r\n    ├─ [0] VM::selectFork(0) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::envString(MNEMONIC) [staticcall]\r\n    │   └─ ← <env var value>\r\n    ├─ [0] VM::deriveKey(<pk>) [staticcall]\r\n    │   └─ ← \"the word `rugueux` is invalid\"\r\n    └─ ← \"the word `rugueux` is invalid\"\r\n\r\n````\r\n\r\nIs there a way to specify language pack to use ?\r\n\r\nFYI tested with the same mnemonic and ethersjs/hardhat, is working fine (despite ethersjs may require to specify the language pack)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
